kind: llman.sdd.spec
name: "tests-ci"
purpose: Describe CI quality gates and required checks for llman.
valid_scope[4]: ".github/workflows/ci.yaml",justfile,"tests/","llmanspec/specs/tests-ci/"
requirements[4]{req_id,title,statement}:
  r1,CI runs fmt and clippy with warnings denied,"CI MUST run format checks and clippy with `-D warnings` as part of the standard check pipeline, and the checks MUST run on the same pinned nightly baseline used by the repository toolchain configuration."
  r2,CI runs a release build check,CI MUST run a release build to ensure the project builds on the same pinned nightly baseline used for local development and quality checks.
  r3,Clippy warnings are addressed in tests,"Test code MUST avoid clippy warnings that would fail `-D warnings` (e.g., prefer `is_empty()` over `len() > 0`)."
  r4,"check-all 包含 schema 校验","`just check-all` MUST 包含 schema 校验步骤，确保生成的 JSON schema 与样例配置有效且可用。"
scenarios[4]{req_id,id,given,when,then}:
  r1,"ci-check-job-uses-pinned-nightly-baseline","",CI runs on main branch,"the check job uses the repository pinned nightly baseline and executes `just check-all` (or an equivalent nightly-based check sequence)"
  r2,"ci-build-job-uses-pinned-nightly-baseline","",CI runs on main branch,"the build job uses the repository pinned nightly baseline and executes `just build-release`"
  r3,"clippy-run","","`cargo +nightly clippy -- -D warnings` runs",test code does not emit len_zero or similar warnings
  r4,"运行-check-all","","开发者运行 `just check-all`","`just check-schemas` 会被执行"
